    "2009; Zheng and Ye 2009; He 2011; Yao et al.",
    "2011; Yang and Yu 2013; Su et al.",
    "2014; Bai and Yu 2016; Zhang and Zheng 2016; Zheng et al. 2018) Train supervised traditional machine learning models, e.g., Naive Bayes Classifers, Support Vector Machines (SVM), Decision Trees, Random Forest, etc., using labeled multilingual sentiment datasets Can capture complex relationships in data, adaptable to various domains, and suitable for medium-sized datasets • Reliance on Annotated Data: The method necessitates labeled training data, which could pose a challenge when acquiring or preparing datasets with accurately annotated sentiments for training purposes • Need for Appropriate Feature Selection: The process requires careful consideration in choosing relevant and effective training features."
